# Privacy Policy for News Publisher App by Superaze

*Effective Date: September 11, 2023*

Thank you for using News Publisher, a Facebook application developed by Superaze. This Privacy Policy outlines the information we collect, how we use it, and your rights in relation to this application.

## 1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our Facebook app, News Publisher. By using News Publisher, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 User Information

We may collect the following information from you:

- **Facebook Profile Information:** We may collect your Facebook profile information, including your name, profile picture, and email address, in accordance with Facebook's policies.

- **Contact Information:** If you choose to contact us, we may collect your name and email address.

### 2.2 News Posts

- **News Source Information:** When you use News Publisher to publish news articles from the Bing News Search API, we may collect information about the source of the news article, including the provider's name.

### 2.3 Usage Data

- **App Usage:** We may collect information about how you use News Publisher, such as which features you use and the frequency of your usage.

## 3. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

- **To Publish News:** We use the Bing News Search API to retrieve news articles and publish them on your Facebook page. We also include credits to the source provider as part of the post.

- **To Provide Support:** If you contact us for support, we will use your contact information to respond to your inquiries.

- **To Improve the App:** We may analyze usage data to enhance the functionality and user experience of News Publisher.

## 4. Sharing Your Information

We do not share your information with third parties, except in the following cases:

- **Compliance with Law:** We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to a valid legal request.

## 5. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

## 6. Your Rights

You have the following rights in relation to your information:

- **Access and Correction:** You can request access to the information we hold about you and ask us to correct any inaccuracies.

- **Data Portability:** You can request a copy of your information in a structured, machine-readable format.

- **Deletion:** You can request that we delete your information, subject to any legal obligations.

## 7. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:

**Email:** [alyment98@gmail.com](mailto:alyment98@gmail.com)

## 8. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the revised policy will be effective from the date of publication.

Please review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.
